TITLE: Accessing Blockchain Storage at a Specific Block Using Subxt Rust
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the updated block-centric approach to accessing blockchain storage via Subxt, showing how to fetch storage entries at a given block hash or latest block. The snippet relies on the new `.at()` API for specifying the block context, replacing the older method of passing an optional block hash directly to storage fetch methods. Dependencies include the Subxt Rust client and the staking_bonded storage entry. The input is the storage key and optional block hash; the output is the fetched storage value for that block.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paritytech/subxt/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
let a = api.storage().at(None).await?.fetch(&staking_bonded).await?;
```

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
let block = api.blocks().at(None).await?;
let a = block.storage().fetch(&staking_bonded, None).await?;
```

