TITLE: Basic Type Substitution in Subxt Codegen (Rust)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the previous method for basic type substitution in Subxt's codegen. This approach uses the `#[subxt::subxt(substitute_type = "...")]` attribute to replace a specific type (`sp_arithmetic::per_things::Foo`) with a local type (`crate::Foo`). This method had limitations regarding matching generic parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paritytech/subxt/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_32

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[subxt::subxt(runtime_metadata_path = "../polkadot_metadata.scale")]
